# Architecture Boundaries

For backend code under `src/`.

- Routes define endpoints and middleware only; no business logic.
- Controllers orchestrate request/response only; keep handlers thin.
- Services contain business logic and policy decisions.
- Models define schema and persistence concerns only.
- Controllers must not perform direct database logic beyond service delegation.
- Services must not depend on Express `req`/`res`.
- Keep cross-layer dependencies one-directional:
  - `routes -> controllers -> services -> models`
- Shared helpers belong in `utils/`; reusable request guards in `middlewares/`.
- Central response and error behavior must use `validations/response.js` and `validations/error.js`.
